### =================== CREATE ===================

### Create a new brand
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/brands
{{authHeader}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Apple",
  "description": "Technology company known for iPhone and Mac computers",
  "website": "https://www.apple.com",
  "logoUrl": "https://example.com/logos/apple.png",
  "isActive": true
}

### Create another brand (minimal fields)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/brands
{{authHeader}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Generic Brand"
}

### =================== READ/LIST ===================

### List brands (paginated, sorted by name ASC)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/brands?page=0&size=20&sortBy=name&sortDir=asc
{{authHeader}}

### List active brands only (paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/brands?active=true&page=0&size=20
{{authHeader}}

### Get all active brands (no pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/brands/active
{{authHeader}}

### Get a brand by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/brands/1
{{authHeader}}

### Search brands by keyword
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/brands?search=apple&page=0&size=10
{{authHeader}}

### =================== UPDATE ===================

### Update brand fields
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/brands/1
{{authHeader}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Apple Inc.",
  "description": "Updated: American multinational technology company",
  "website": "https://www.apple.com/updated",
  "logoUrl": "https://example.com/logos/apple-updated.png",
  "isActive": true
}

### Deactivate (soft delete) via update
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/brands/1
{{authHeader}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "isActive": false
}

### =================== DELETE (SOFT) ===================

### Soft delete a brand by ID (sets inactive)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/brands/2
{{authHeader}}

### =================== AUTOCOMPLETE & FILTERS ===================

### Autocomplete by prefix
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/brands/autocomplete?query=ap&limit=10
{{authHeader}}

### Brands with website only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/brands/with-website
{{authHeader}}

### Brands with logo only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/brands/with-logo
{{authHeader}}
